# SkincareHunt

SkincareHunt is a full-stack web application designed to find the best discounts on the latest skincare products. By integrating Django on the backend, PostgreSQL as the database, and Next.js (v13) with TypeScript on the frontend, SkincareHunt leverages BeautifulSoup for data scraping, delivering real-time skincare deals to users.

## 🌟 Features

- **Real-time Web Scraping**: Employing BeautifulSoup to frequently scrape and showcase the freshest skincare deals.
- **User-Driven Filters**: Empower users to sift through products based on their specific needs.
- **Instant Updates**: Ensuring users always have access to the most up-to-date deals.

## 🛠 Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites

- **Node.js & npm**: Ensure Node.js and npm are installed. If not, [download them here](https://nodejs.org/en/download/).
- **Python**: As SkincareHunt uses Django for its backend, [Python is essential](https://www.python.org/downloads/).
- **PostgreSQL**: [Set up PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org/download/).

### 🔧 Setup

#### 1. Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/skincarehunt.git
cd skincarehunt
```

### 2. Setting up the Frontend:

# Head into the frontend directory
cd frontend

# Install necessary dependencies
npm install

# Start the development server
npm run dev

### 3. Setting up the Backend:

# Open a different terminal instance/tab and get to the skincarehunt directory:

# Navigate into the back directory
cd back

# Install the Python dependencies. Consider using a virtual environment!
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Migrate the database
python manage.py migrate

# Run the Django server
python manage.py runserver

Your backend should now be active at [http://localhost:8000](http://localhost:8000).

## 📖 Usage

Once both servers are up:

- Visit the frontend to browse the freshest skincare deals.
- Leverage the filters to streamline your search based on your preferences.

